# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# AI Student Agent — environment template
#
# Copy to `.env` for local dev (`cp .env.example .env`) and fill in real values,
# OR enter these as Variables in the Railway dashboard for production.
# `.env` itself is gitignored — never commit real secrets.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ══ REQUIRED: Supabase ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# From Supabase dashboard → Project Settings → API.
# Auth fails closed (HTTP 503) if SUPABASE_URL + SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY are missing.
SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR-PROJECT.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-public-key
SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY=your-service-role-key          # secret — bypasses RLS, server-side only
SUPABASE_JWT_SECRET=your-jwt-secret                 # Project Settings → API → JWT Settings
SUPABASE_USER_ID=00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001  # fallback user (CLI / dev-no-auth only)

# ══ REQUIRED: LLM providers ══════════════════════════════════════════════════
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-proj-...
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# ══ Production: frontend origin (CORS) ═══════════════════════════════════════
# Lock CORS to your deployed frontend URL. Comma-separate multiple origins.
# Leave unset (defaults to "*") for local dev. Set this AFTER the first deploy,
# once you know the Railway-assigned domain.
# FRONTEND_ORIGIN=https://your-app.up.railway.app

# ══ Optional: model selection ════════════════════════════════════════════════
# CHAT_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5          # chat orchestrator (routing); bump to sonnet if needed
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini
# EMBEDDING_MODEL=text-embedding-3-small
# RAG_TOP_K=5

# ══ Optional: rate limiting ══════════════════════════════════════════════════
# In-memory storage is fine for a SINGLE uvicorn worker (the default deploy).
# Point RATELIMIT_STORAGE_URI at redis://… ONLY if you scale to multiple workers.
# RATELIMIT_ENABLED=1
# RATELIMIT_CHAT=15/minute
# RATELIMIT_HEAVY=5/minute
# RATELIMIT_HEAVY_DAILY=50/day
# RATELIMIT_STORAGE_URI=memory://

# ══ Optional: payload guards (bytes / chars) ═════════════════════════════════
# MAX_REQUEST_BYTES=524288000          # 500 MB total request body
# MAX_UPLOAD_FILE_BYTES=52428800       # 50 MB per uploaded file
# MAX_TEXT_CHARS=50000                 # free-text field cap

# ══ Optional: data paths / logging (defaults are fine on Railway) ════════════
# These dirs are ephemeral scratch only (real state lives in Supabase) — leaving
# defaults is correct for a stateless deploy.
# DATA_RAW_PATH=data/raw
# DATA_PROCESSED_PATH=data/processed
# DATA_EXPORTS_PATH=data/exports
# LOG_LEVEL=INFO
# LOG_FILE=

# ══ Local-only tooling (do NOT set in production) ════════════════════════════
# OBSIDIAN_VAULT=
# POPPLER_PATH=

# ══ DANGER — dev only ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# DEV_NO_AUTH disables authentication entirely. It only takes effect when
# Supabase is ALSO absent. NEVER set this in production.
# DEV_NO_AUTH=0
